high.mackenzie.autumn.lang.compiler.compilers

Class ExpressionCodeGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • high.mackenzie.autumn.lang.compiler.compilers.AbstractAstVisitor
      • high.mackenzie.autumn.lang.compiler.compilers.ExpressionCodeGenerator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IAstVisitor
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    StatementCodeGenerator

    public class ExpressionCodeGenerator
extends AbstractAstVisitor
    An instance of this class performs the bytecode generation related to an expression.

      • compileCondition

        protected final void compileCondition(IExpression condition)
        This method generalizes the compilation of a condition expression.

        The condition will be evaluated, and automatically boxed or unboxed when necessary.

        Parameters:
        condition - is the expression that is really a condition.

      • convert

        protected final void convert(IType type,
           IExpression expression)
        This method generates bytecode that converts an expression's value to another type.

        The generated bytecode expects that the expression's value is the topmost value on the operand-stack.

        Parameters:
        type - is the type to which the value will be converted.
        expression - is the expression whose value is being converted.
